<TITLE>Seldy </TITLE>
</HEAD>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/townhall/paper2.jpg">
<center>[ <A HREF ="pres.html">Previous</A> | <A HREF ="intern.html">Next</A> ] 
<br></center><br>
<IMG SRC="seldy.jpg" HSPACE=10 VSPACE=10 align = left><H2> Seldy</H2>

Where would we be without, Seldy?  Almost a member of the family, Seldy is to us what R2D2
was to Luke Skywalker.   The Town Hall site runs on this high-tech piece of equipment.  What
this means to you is speedy access to our information.  So when you request an image by
clicking on a link, our friend, Seldy, delivers it.<p>
Seldy is a Digital Alpha Server 2100 model 4/275 running Digital Unix (OSF/1) 3.2.  It currently
is configured with one 275 MHz Alpha RISC processor, 128 Meg RAM, 5 two gig hard drives,
blah, blah, blah.  When the time comes, we'll pop in some more RAM, processors, and hard
drives.<p>


By the way, where did the name "Seldy" come from anyway?  Come up with your own theory,
send it to <A HREF="mailto:seldy@townhall.com">seldy@townhall.com</A>, and you could
win your very own tasty Moon Pie(tm)!  We will randomly select the winner from a pool of
correct<A NAME="contest"> answers.<p></A>
<br>

