<p>
<H2> Information Marketing Department</H2>
<HR>
<P>
Heritage has created the new Information Marketing department to provide members of Congress, congressional staff, and others in the public policy arena with new ways to access Heritage ideas.
<P>
Information Marketing operates Heritage's popular Web site, <a href="/heritage"><i>www.heritage.org</i></a>, which puts the <a href="/heritage/library">library</a> of Heritage research, free of charge, at the fingertips of everyone with access to the Internet. It also publishes the papers and books that Heritage analysts produce in a variety of ways, both electronically and in print, all designed to facilitate access to Heritage's ideas. Information Marketing produces CD-ROMs, charts, slides, and transparencies, as well as a number of other derivative products. One new format is the "policy pocket card," which provides factual digests of Heritage's most important papers. Members of Congress and their staff have found the cards useful to provide quick references for speeches or to address inquiries from constituents or the media. Early in 1997, Heritage will install a new service to provide faxes of our papers on call 24 hours a day.
<P>

Information Marketing also works with all departments at Heritage to develop themes and focus for domestic and foreign policy issues, and it helps to coordinate activities, products, and events at Heritage to maximize their impact. All of Information Marketing's activities are directed at providing you with the information you need in the form you need it -- <I>whenever</I> you need it. Information Marketing continually conducts research to help Heritage more effective produce the products that target Heritage's ideas and focus research on those issues that that advance conservative ideas.
<P>
Please call Heritage's Publication Sales office at (202) 608-6260 or send e-mail <a href="mailto:pubs@heritage.org">pubs@heritage.org</a> to receive copies of any Heritage publication. Or log on to <a href="/heritage/"><i>www.heritage.org</i></a> to download the publications you need at any time of day.
<P>

For a more thorough description of the Information Marketing department, or to suggest additional information products that would be helpful to you, please contact Ann Klucsarits at (202) 608-6188, or email <a href="mailto:klucsaritsa@heritage.org">klucsaritsa@heritage.org</a>
<P>

