<html>
<head>
<title>Lugar Proposes A National Sales Tax
Press Release From the Office of the Senator</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/townhall/paper2.jpg">
<br>
<br>
<p>
<center>
<h3>Lugar Proposes A National Sales Tax<br>
Press Release From the Office of the Senator</h3>
</center>
<br>
<br>
<p>
U.S. Sen. Richard Lugar will tell a congressional committee today that the best way to increase wages, spur robust cconomic growth and reduce federal government intrusion in Americans' lives is to abolish the income tax and replace it with a national sales tax.<p>
"It is time to stop working around the edges of the tax code.  We must transform it completely. By taxing savings and investment at least twice, the tax system has become the biggest impediment to economic growth," Lugar said.<p>
Representative Bill Archer, Chairman of the House Ways and Means Committee, and Lugar advocate instituting a national sales tax that would tax the purchase of goods and services rather than income. Such a consumption tax would encourage savings and investment because people would be taxed only on the money they spend, "Our net national savings rate has reached alarmingly low levels. Because of this low rate of savings, capital to fuel our economy has become increasingly scarce. "  Lugar cited a Concord Coalition Study that estimates annual median family income would be $50,000, instead of the current S35.000, if U.S. productivity had maintained its pre-1974 level of 2.9 percent per year. It is currently 1.1 percent.<p>
The simplicity of a national sales tax makes it thc most effective and appealing way to reform the current tax system, Lugar said, "The burden of complying with thc Income tax code would be lifted. The money you make is your own. You don't have to report it or hide it."<p>
Such a straightforward approach to taxation would substantially reduce the role of the lnternal Revenue System. The income tax represents the worst form of intrusion into the lives of citizens, Lugar said. Each year, Americans spend more than five billion hours of time to comply with it. "The IRS would no longer look ovcr thc shoulder of every American. There will be no audits. Arnericans will not waste time and effort worrying about record keeping, deductions or exemptions that are part of the current tax code."<p>
In order to avoid placing a greater tax burden on low-income Americans, exemptions could be established for a certain annual dollar amount of purchases or categories of purchases, such as food, medicine and housing.<p>
<br>
<br>
[ <a href=":/townhall/spotlight/t-spot.html">Spotlights</a> ]
</body>
